;Introduction
Réamhrá


;The Internet is becoming an increasingly important part of our lives.
Is cuid thábhachtach dár saol é an tIdirlíon, níos tábhachtaí chuile lá.


;The Mozilla project is a global community of people who believe that openness, innovation, and opportunity are key to the continued health of the Internet. We have worked together since 1998 to ensure that the Internet is developed in a way that benefits everyone. We are best known for creating the Mozilla Firefox web browser.
Is éard atá i dtionscadal Mozilla ná comhphobal domhanda a chreideann gurb iad an oscailteacht, an nuálaíocht, agus deiseanna na rudaí a chinnteoidh sláinte an Idirlín san fhadtréimhse. Táimid ag obair le chéile ó 1998 chun deimhniú go bhforbraítear an tIdirlíon ar leas an phobail. Is fearr aithne orainn as an mbrabhsálaí Mozilla Firefox.


;The Mozilla project uses a community-based approach to create world-class open source software and to develop new types of collaborative activities. We create communities of people involved in making the Internet experience better for all of us.
Baineann tionscadal Mozilla úsáid as cur chuige pobalbhunaithe chun bogearraí den chéad scoth a chruthú agus chun gníomhaíochtaí comhoibríocha a fhorbairt. Cruthaímid comhphobail atá ag iarraidh feabhas a chur ar an Idirlíon ar ár son uilig.


;As a result of these efforts, we have distilled a set of principles that we believe are critical for the Internet to continue to benefit the public good as well as commercial aspects of life. We set out these principles below.
De thoradh na n-iarrachtaí seo, táimid tar éis liosta prionsabal a leagan amach, prionsabail atá fíorthábhachtach do thodhchaí an Idirlín mar acmhainn a dhéanann leas don phobal agus don saol gnó chomh maith. Leagaimid na prionsabail seo amach thíos.


;The goals for the Manifesto are to:
Seo iad aidhmeanna an Fhorógra:


;articulate a vision for the Internet that Mozilla participants want the Mozilla Foundation to pursue;
fís don Idirlíon a leagan amach, fís a dtacaíonn rannpháirtithe Mozilla léi agus ceann a n-oibreoidh Fondúireacht Mhozilla ina threo;


;speak to people whether or not they have a technical background;
gach duine a spreagadh, beag beann ar a c(h)úlra sa teicneolaíocht;


;make Mozilla contributors proud of what we're doing and motivate us to continue; and
bród a chothú i rannpháirtithe Mozilla as an obair atá á déanamh againn; agus


;provide a framework for other people to advance this vision of the Internet.
creatlach oibre a thabhairt do dhaoine chun an fhís seo a chur chun cinn.


;These principles will not come to life on their own. People are needed to make the Internet open and participatory - people acting as individuals, working together in groups, and leading others. The Mozilla Foundation is committed to advancing the principles set out in the Mozilla Manifesto. We invite others to join us and make the Internet an ever better place for everyone.
Ní thiocfaidh na prionsabail seo chun beatha ina n-aonar. Daoine amháin atá in ann an tIdirlíon a choinneáil oscailte agus daonlathach — daoine ina n-aonar, daoine ag obair i ngrúpaí, agus daoine ag spreagadh daoine eile. Tá Fondúireacht Mhozilla go hiomlán tugtha do na prionsabail atá leagtha amach i bhForógra Mozilla. Fearaimid fáilte roimh éinne atá ag iarraidh obair a dhéanamh linn chun feabhas a chur ar an Idirlíon.


